			div.post-content
				div.post-section-container#creating-a-jenkinsfile
					h2.section-title Creating a Jenkinsfile
					div.post-image-container
						a.post-image-container(href="https://www.jenkins.io/images/logo-title-opengraph.png")
							img.post-image(src="https://www.jenkins.io/images/logo-title-opengraph.png" alt="jenkins")
						figcaption.post-image-caption Jenkins Image from Jenkins Website
					p.post-details When creating a Jenkinsfile the necessary fields must are: pipeline, agent, stages. "pipeline" is always needed and is at the top-level. From here we have the "agent" which describes where to execute (default would be set to any). Then we have stages which describes where the works happens, and within "stages" you define "stage" that will have parameters such as: ("init"), ("build"), ("test"), and ("deploy").
					p.post-details Another field that may be added and this is added after "stages". This is "post" and what this does is execute some logic after all stages have executed. The conditions that are within the "post" section are: always, success, failure. Always will always execute whether the script failed or not. Examples of this are sending emails out to the team after a build.
				div.post-section-container#adding-environmental-variables
					h2.section-title Adding Environmental Variables
					p.post-details In order to add environmental variables to your file, before "stages" you need to add "environment" into your pipeline.
					p.post-details 
						div.code-snippet-container
							div.code-snippet-header
								h5.code-snippet-title jenkins_file_env
								button.copy-bttn
									img.copy-icon(src="/images/copy-icon.png")
							div.code-snippet-body
								pre.language-jenkins
									code.language-jenkins
										span.code-specific pipeline 
										.
											{
										br
										span.code-specific(class="indent-1") agent 
										span.indent-1 any
										br
										span.code-specific(class="indent-1") environment 
										span.indent-1 {
										br
										span.indent-2 EXAMPLE_VAR = 'Something'
										br
										span.indent-1 }
										br
										span.indent-1 ...
										br
										span.indent-1 }
										br
				div.post-section-container#adding-build-tools-for-project
